The first all-pair scan was doing interaction regressions for every candidate pair and timed out. I’ve already got the strongest main effects for the first several outcomes; now I’m rerunning the heterogeneity search in a lighter form that tests all pair subgroups and then refines the strongest pairs into three-predicate subgroups.
